Data adjustment

Sum of retention performance

SPACE01_data_Masterarbeit$total_count <- SPACE01_data_Masterarbeit$recall_count + SPACE01_data_Masterarbeit$open.questions_count + SPACE01_data_Masterarbeit$transfer.questions_count

Data exclusion

The following exclusion criteria are applied, based on a prior online data collection:
1. Incomplete participation.
2. Participated in the same study (participation_already).
3. Used external resources (external.help_poststudy, external.help_spaced.poststudy2)
4. Participants will be excluded from the final analyses, if they had a low recall performance (x i < M i 2.5 MAD) on the recall test in Learning Block 3 or at least the proportion of correctly recalled information being less than .1, with x i = n original observations, M = Median, MAD = Mean Absolute Deviation = b M i (|x i M j (xj )|), and b = 1.4826 AND fulfill one of the following conditions below (a-d):
a. Participants are not fluent in German (i.e., they are not native in German, or moved to Germany or a German-speaking country before they were 16).
b. Participants report to be either too distracted from their environment (disturbed_poststudy OR disturbed_poststudy1 OR disturbed_spaced.poststudy2 with 8 OR more on a 10-point Likert response scale) AND they could not sufficiently focus on the experiment (concentration_poststudy or concentration_poststudy1 or concentration_spaced.poststudy2 with 3 or less on a 10-point Likert response scale).
c.Participants chose the items that they did not seriously participate and process the tasks in the study.
d.Participants provide in the free comment box that they were not motivated or did not participate seriously.

Lambdas recall

  1. Calculating means:
    recall_count
    moma: 3.13
    mospa: 4.10
    muma: 4.34
    muspa: 3.59

  2. Overall mean:
    (3.13 + 4.1 + 4.34 + 3.59) / 4 = 3.79

  3. Calculating Lambdas:
    moma: 3.13 - 3.79 = -0.66
    mospa: 4.10 - 3.79 = 0.31
    muma: 4.34 - 3.79 = 0.55
    muspa: 3.59 - 3.79 = -0.2

  4. Testing if sum is 0:
    -0.66 + 0.31 + 0.55 + (-0.2) = 0

Lambdas open.questions

  1. Calculating means:
    recall_count
    moma: 1.96
    mospa: 2.37
    muma: 2.26
    muspa: 2.33

  2. Overall mean:
    (1.96 + 2.37 + 2.26 + 2.33) / 4 = 2.23

  3. Calculating Lambdas:
    moma: 1.96 - 2.23 = -0.27
    mospa: 2.37 - 2.23 = 0.14
    muma: 2.26 - 2.23 = 0.03
    muspa: 2.33 - 2.23 = 0.1

  4. Testing if sum is 0:
    -0.27 + 0.14 + 0.03 + 0.1 = 0

Lambdas transfer.questions

  1. Calculating means:
    recall_count
    moma: 4.13
    mospa: 4.61
    muma: 4.45
    muspa: 4.0

  2. Overall mean:
    (4.13 + 4.61 + 4.45 + 4.0) / 4 = 4.2975

  3. Calculating Lambdas:
    moma: 4.13 - 4.2975 = -0.1675
    mospa: 4.61 - 4.2975 = 0.3125
    muma: 4.45 - 4.2975 = 0.1525
    muspa: 4.0 - 4.2975 = -0.2975

  4. Testing if sum is 0:
    -0.1675 + 0.3125 + 0.1525 + (-0.2975) = 0

Contrasts for Hypotheses

Hypothesis 1 Spacing effect:
Hypothesis 1.1: Spacing leads to a higher recall performance after 1 week compared to massed learning of monomedia texts.
Hypothesis 1.2: Spacing leads to a similar recall performance after 1 week compared to massed learning of monomedia texts.

Hypothesis 2 Multimedia effect:
Hypothesis 1.1: Learning with multimedia material leads to a higher recall performance after 1 week than learning with monomedia text in the massed learning group.
Hypothesis 1.2: Learning with multimedia material leads to a similar recall performance after 1 week than learning with monomedia text in the massed learning group.

Hypothesis 3 Antagonistic interaction of spacing and multimedia effect:
Hypothesis 3: Combining spacing and multimedia material leads to similar retention performance.
